page.title: 10AN ENJOYABLE SPOT IN KEELBY
page.content: My favourite place which I enjoy going to most is called Stones's.It is a stream with grassy banks and fields surrounding it.I have a friend called Phil who lives near the place and we go from Phil's house around the edge of a field.Then we come to a pipe going across the stream as one of the banks is to steep.We walk on the bank so that we avoid mucking up the water.This means we see anything that goes by.When we see an old bag or brick we lift it up because there are often newts and if we are lucky a frog. Once we lifted up a tyre and there were about 5 newts.
